abstract: The United States will provide financial assistance to Ethiopia as it pursues political reforms, the office of Ethiopian Prime Minister Abiy Ahmed said on Tuesday during a visit by U.S. Secretary of State Mike Pompeo.
snippet: The United States will provide financial assistance to Ethiopia as it pursues political reforms, the office of Ethiopian Prime Minister Abiy Ahmed said on Tuesday during a visit by U.S. Secretary of State Mike Pompeo.
lead_paragraph: ADDIS ABABA — The United States will provide financial assistance to Ethiopia as it pursues political reforms, the office of Ethiopian Prime Minister Abiy Ahmed said on Tuesday during a visit by U.S. Secretary of State Mike Pompeo.
headline_main: U.S. to Offer Financial Support for Ethiopia Political Reforms: PM
headline_print_headline: U.S. to Offer Financial Support for Ethiopia Political Reforms: PM

abstract: After garnering 19 percent support in a national poll, the billionaire will be on the debate stage, where he is certain to be a target of onstage criticism.
snippet: After garnering 19 percent support in a national poll, the billionaire will be on the debate stage, where he is certain to be a target of onstage criticism.
lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — Former Mayor Michael R. Bloomberg of New York has qualified for the next two Democratic debates, including one on Wednesday in Las Vegas. It will be his first appearance onstage alongside his presidential rivals.

abstract: The value of the expected agreement between the United States and the Taliban lies in opening the door to an Afghan peace process.
snippet: The value of the expected agreement between the United States and the Taliban lies in opening the door to an Afghan peace process.
lead_paragraph: The talks between the United States and the Taliban in Doha, Qatar, which were abruptly canceled by President Trump in September, are back on track. After several months of diplomatic regrouping, American and Taliban negotiators are once again on the verge of sealing a deal.

abstract: He may be running as the anti-Trump, but when it comes to the politics of racial control, there is a resemblance.
snippet: He may be running as the anti-Trump, but when it comes to the politics of racial control, there is a resemblance.
lead_paragraph: Donald Trump is who he is as a politician because of his unapologetically racial vision of the American nation. Trump’s America is white, and he sees his job as protecting that whiteness from black and brown people who might come to the country or claim greater status within it. That’s what it meant to “make America great again.” And he’s delivered, using the power of the office and the force of the state to attack and stigmatize black and brown people, from outspoken celebrities to ordinary immigrants.

abstract: Ms. Warren’s campaign and her allies, convinced her message is being ignored, see a path forward — and they say writing her off would be a mistake.
snippet: Ms. Warren’s campaign and her allies, convinced her message is being ignored, see a path forward — and they say writing her off would be a mistake.
lead_paragraph: RENO, Nev. — A bad month for Senator Elizabeth Warren of Massachusetts keeps getting worse. She finished in a respectable third place in the Iowa caucuses, but a results-tallying meltdown muddled what could have been a good evening. New Hampshire was better at logistics but worse for her candidacy, considering she ended up closer to candidates who dropped out after the primary than those who finished on top.

abstract: The president’s tweets, Bill Barr’s doings and the contest for the Democratic nomination made for quite a week of political theater.
snippet: The president’s tweets, Bill Barr’s doings and the contest for the Democratic nomination made for quite a week of political theater.
lead_paragraph: Bret Stephens: Katie Barr the door, Gail! That was quite a public rebuke of Donald Trump from Attorney General Bill Barr, who said the president’s incessant tweeting was making his job “impossible.”

abstract: He is driving the country to financial ruin. And his own party is letting it happen.
snippet: He is driving the country to financial ruin. And his own party is letting it happen.
lead_paragraph: People have a tragic flaw: Sometimes we want others to do the thinking for us. And across the ages promoters and con men have been more than willing to oblige. They invite us to indulge in the fantasy that a newfound father figure will fix it all, though it never works out that way.

headline_main: Why Do My Fellow Republicans Make Excuses for Trump’s Deficits?

abstract: The Montana education system was designed for fairness and pulling together. The justices should appreciate that legacy.
snippet: The Montana education system was designed for fairness and pulling together. The justices should appreciate that legacy.
lead_paragraph: Scrutinizing the avuncular sphinx Chief Justice John Roberts throughout the impeachment trial of President Trump, I kept wondering whether he will preserve or ransack the legacy of the framers we revere — framers like the Republican Betty Babcock and the Democrat Dorothy Eck. It’s the question on all Americans’ minds: Do Mr. Roberts and his eight co-workers fully appreciate the public-spirited grandeur of the winter of 1971-72, when 100 Montanans, including housewives, ministers, a veterinarian and a beekeeper, gathered at the state capital, Helena, for the constitutional convention, affectionately nicknamed the “Con Con”?

abstract: Mayors’ offices, city councils and Congress are flooded with young people. In “The Ones We’ve Been Waiting For,” Charlotte Alter explains why.
